This paper proposes a deep learning approach for automatic classification of seizures against non-seizures using electroencephalography (EEG) signals. The approach leverages an attention mechanism and a bidirectional long short-term memory (BiLSTM) to capture both spatial and temporal discriminating features. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
